  "subject": "Remove APPC dependencies to unblock Spring Boot 3 migration",
  "commit_message": "Remove APPC dependencies to unblock Spring Boot 3 migration\n\nThe APPC client libraries (org.onap.appc.client v1.7.2) have no Java 17\ncompatible release, blocking the Spring Boot 3 migration. APPC is not\ndeployed in the running cluster and SDNC/CDS serve as alternatives.\n\nThis removes:\n- adapters/so-appc-orchestrator module entirely\n- All APPC client classes from MSOCommonBPMN and common modules\n- APPC-only BPMN workflows (RollbackVnf, VnfInPlaceUpdate, VnfConfigUpdate,\n  UpdateVnfInfra, UpdateVfModuleInfraV2, ReplaceVnfInfra, DoUpdateVnfAndModules)\n- 15 VNF Activity building blocks and GenericVnfHealthCheckBB/ConfigurationScaleOutBB\n- APPC decision point controllers and task implementations\n- All org.onap.appc.client dependency declarations\n\nThe default controller actor fallback changes from \"APPC\" to \"CDS\" in\nControllerExecution.java for PNF and VNF scopes.\n\nIssue-ID: SO-4365\nChange-Id: I62a4afcf618ebf9609ba52497fab583ab257875f\nSigned-off-by: Fiete Ostkamp <fiete.ostkamp@telekom.de>\n",
